=========================================================
Step 5 : Virtual Function Call
=========================================================

ptr->display();

Compiler DOES NOT directly call

Base::display()

Instead it generates conceptually

ptr

↓

vptr

↓

vtable

↓

display()

↓

Derived::display()

Therefore

Output

Derived

=========================================================
Runtime Flow
=========================================================

ptr->display()

↓

Read object's vptr

↓

Locate vtable

↓

Find display()

↓

Call corresponding function

↓

Execute Derived::display()

